Dovyalis hebecarpa

   [5536.jpg]
    Authority   (Gardner) Warb.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Violales:Flacourtiaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 5536

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A dioecious shrub or small tree reaching 4-7 m in
   height, with spiny branches. Fruit a subglobose berry, up to 2.5 cm in
   diameter, maroon-purple and pubescent. USES The fruits are mostly used
   for making preserves as the are often too sour and astringent to be
   eaten raw. GROWING PERIOD Perennial. Begins to bear 3-4 years after
   sowing. COMMON NAMES Ketembilla, Ceylon Gooseberry, Ketembillier,
   Groseillier de Ceylon, Quetembila. FURTHER INF Ketembilla is native of
   Sri Lanka and India. It is grown throughout tropical Asia, particularly
   India and Sri Lanka. It prefer a high air humidity and it require a
   good supply of warter during fruit development.

   Sources
   SOURCES (D. hebecarpa (Gardner) Warb.)
   Atta M 1990 pp 53
   Popenoe W 1974 pp 443-445 [USE, TEMP, DRA,
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 205 [USE, DRA, RAIN, TEMP]
   Duke J 1975 pp 15 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Verheij E 1991 pp 329 [USE]

